name: Chicken and Dumplings III
author: Melissa
summary: My mom used to make this recipe for us growing up. Now I make it for my family and they all love it! It's simple yet delicious! Enjoy!
ingredients: 2 (10.75 ounce) cans  condensed cream of celery soup
directions: In a large pot over high heat, combine the chicken with enough water to cover, and boil for 15 to 20 minutes
Drain some of the water from the pot, reserving 3 cups in the pot
Remove chicken and allow it to cool, then pull it apart into bite size pieces; return to pot
Reduce heat to medium, and add the cans of condensed soup
Pull the biscuit dough into pieces, and add to the soup
Simmer over medium heat for 7 to 8 minutes, or until the dough is cooked through
